msgid "Shorthand for `Client.get_reply_to_message`."
msgstr ""

#: 856c2047ab9a4205b2d4acc2ffc6c276 grammers.custom.Message.grouped_id:1 of
msgid ""
"If this message belongs to a group of messages, return the unique "
"identifier for that group."
msgstr ""

#: c5600db886f44da388710a0303a0649e grammers.custom.Message.grouped_id:4 of
msgid "This applies to albums of media, such as multiple photos grouped together."
msgstr ""

#: 7acce28eac054a65a7c461882e14e59e grammers.custom.Message.grouped_id:6 of
msgid ""
"Note that there may be messages sent in between the messages forming a "
"group."
msgstr ""

#: 370f5c0e135b4887b8773a714af5ef59 grammers.custom.Message.id:1 of
msgid "The ID of this message."
msgstr ""

#: 0199c1846b9344b992dcf8f29462e099 grammers.custom.Message.id:3 of
msgid ""
"Message identifiers are counters that start at 1 and grow by 1 for each "
"message produced."
msgstr ""

#: 37a5352033f34af89ba8acb55d3d3d58 grammers.custom.Message.id:5 of
msgid ""
"Every channel has its own unique message counter. This counter is the "
"same for all users, but unique to each channel."
msgstr ""

#: 63561c48b2e245719638d8c2253b4db9 grammers.custom.Message.id:8 of
msgid ""
"Every account has another unique message counter which is used for "
"private conversations and small group chats. This means different "
"accounts will likely have different message identifiers for the same "
"message in a private conversation or small group chat. This also implies "
"that the message identifier alone is enough to uniquely identify the "
"message, without the need to know the chat ID."
msgstr ""

#: 6d1c3b9425474ae696c466dab32707af grammers.custom.Message.id:14 of
msgid ""
"**You cannot use the message ID of User A when running as User B**, "
"unless this message belongs to a megagroup or broadcast channel. Beware "
"of this when using methods like [`Client::delete_messages`], which "
"**cannot** validate the peer where the message should be deleted for "
"those cases."
msgstr ""

#: e774056239e746d184936bf6022e42ef grammers.custom.Message.invert_media:1 of
msgid ""
"If set, any eventual webpage preview will be shown on top of the message "
"instead of at the bottom."
msgstr ""

#: 8b49715816ec44cca8e6a38c6b919193 grammers.custom.Message.legacy:1 of
msgid "it has to be refetched with the new layer."
