"Indicating that due to the high cost of SMS verification codes for the "
"user's country/provider, the user must purchase a Telegram Premium "
"subscription in order to proceed with the login/signup."
msgstr ""

#: dcdefb5c660d46adbb5e5df4e125333d grammers.client.PeerMap:1 of
msgid "Helper structure to efficiently retrieve peers via their peer."
msgstr ""

#: b78f1bf0bca14b05948c5af6349c5c36 grammers.client.PeerMap:3 of
msgid ""
"A lot of responses include the peers related to them in the form of a "
"list of users and peers, making it annoying to extract a specific peer. "
"This structure lets you save those separate vectors in a single place and"
" query them by using a `Peer`."
msgstr ""

#: 824ae935dbcf4c348e546f07e02f1780 grammers.client.PeerMap:7 of
msgid ""
"While this type derives `Clone` for convenience, it is recommended to use"
" [`PeerMap::handle`] instead to signal that it is a cheap clone."
msgstr ""

#: 09bfcf54ac2a486d8c5b720d463cdcdd grammers.client.Platform:1 of
msgid "Platform Identifier referenced only by [`RestrictionReason`]."
msgstr ""

#: bef8e4719b1d4f28bef037eca6b2f103 grammers.client.RestrictionReason:1 of
msgid "Reason why a user is globally restricted."
msgstr ""

#: 423ad28c999a4d949c1938d8ecd9e58f grammers.errors.SignInError:1 of
msgid "Login-related errors."
msgstr ""

#: 512d933263d34320916bbc4c2c5aa0e2 grammers.errors.SignUpRequiredError:1 of
msgid ""
"Sign-up with an official client is required. (Third-party applications "
"cannot be used to register new accounts.)"
msgstr ""

#: 350f4c52ad7543b9959f85f77882b975 grammers.client.User:1 of
msgid "A user."
msgstr ""

#: 250134dc515b45f8be9aa0e8f7c655bb grammers.client.User:3 of
msgid ""
"Users include your contacts, members of a group, bot accounts created by "
"[@BotFather], or anyone with a Telegram account."
msgstr ""

#: e2608ef0ad1f4558bc50c7eb86edf20e grammers.client.User:6 of
msgid ""
"A \"normal\" (non-bot) user may also behave like a \"bot\" without "
"actually being one, for example, when controlled with a program as "
"opposed to being controlled by a human through a Telegram application. "
"These are commonly known as \"userbots\", and some people use them to "
"enhance their Telegram experience (for example, creating \"commands\" so "
